Thanks in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/19/01 10:14:29 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Partnering with a good Ol Druid</span><hr size=1> when you have a druid partner you can do all kinds of interesting quads. Basically - add 4 to your level and quad what people that level do. the exp is pretty good and its a lot of fun. I was duo-quadding wyverns with druid or wizzies friends as early as level 45.<br>
<br>
Duo-quadding is not really that hard - just remember that if you keep running in a straight line with eachother then you don't have to worry about who has agro. Splitting up a quad is a very bad thing. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: arial"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor Kilbringer</b></a><br>Evoker of the 59th Conclave<br><span style="font-size: 10px">Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b><br>
